{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f67dc52b-c359-44a9-b434-972f0f75a399","content":"The bug is clear — `ProcessPayment` only rejects zero, not negative amounts (line 29). Here's the fastest workflow: use **`dotnet watch test`** which auto-reruns tests on every file save — no manual rebuild needed.\n\nLet me start it and then apply the fix:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01RkEczD1sLUaUbxWrN1SXsG","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Setting up watch workflow"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_012dECh5k3TkX5TWj6LoiZGc","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-657608d4dbee49a1b9242f3bc90b4e77 && dotnet watch test --filter \"ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\" 2>&1","description":"Start dotnet watch test for the failing test","mode":"async","shellId":"watch-test"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Start dotnet watch test for the failing test"}],"interactionId":"70b0bbc0-f63e-4ccb-8c72-400e3712903b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants the fastest workflow to iterate on the fix. The best approach is `dotnet watch test` which will automatically re-run tests when files change. Let me start that up and also fix the bug.\n\nThe bug is clear: `ProcessPayment` only checks for `amount == 0` but doesn't check for negative amounts. The fix is to add `if (amount < 0)` or change the condition to `amount <= 0`.\n\nLet me start `dotnet watch test` with a filter for just that test, so they can see it fail, then fix it and see it pass automatically.","outputTokens":416,"requestId":"4C3B:180676:C9B54E:F838F3:6A01328F"},"id":"b63863fb-044f-4e1e-9233-57a605496682","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:36:24.607Z","parentId":"678031ac-e5b0-47c3-8e96-f33325422d6f"}
